   <concept id="FAR_31_205_30" class="- topic/topic concept/concept " xtrc="">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">31.205-30</ph> Patent costs.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d1960e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1985e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
						            The following patent costs are allowable to the extent that they are incurred as requirements of a Government contract (but see <xref href="31.205-33.dita#FAR_31_205_33"
                        base="i1085371"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">31.205-33</xref>):</p>
               <ol id="d1960e26" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1985e19">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
								                Costs of preparing invention disclosures, reports, and other documents.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1985e24">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
								                Costs for searching the art to the extent necessary to make the invention disclosures.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1985e29">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
								                Other costs in connection with the filing and prosecution of a United States patent application where title or royalty-free license is to be conveyed to the Government.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1985e34">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
						            General counseling services relating to patent matters, such as advice on patent laws, regulations, clauses, and employee agreements, are allowable (but see <xref href="31.205-33.dita#FAR_31_205_33"
                        base="i1085371"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">31.205-33</xref>).</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1985e42">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
						            Other than those for general counseling services, patent costs not required by the contract are unallowable. (See also <xref href="31.205-37.dita#FAR_31_205_37"
                        base="i1085501"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">31.205-37</xref>.)</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
</dita>
